meanings":["From the Latin form, <i>Io(h)anna</i>, of Greek <i>Iōanna</i>, the feminine equivalent of <i>Iōannēs</i> (  see  John  ). In the New Testament, this name is borne by a woman who was one of Jesus's followers (Luke 8:3; 24:10). She was the wife of the steward of the household of King Herod Antipas. The name was regularly used throughout the Middle Ages in most parts of Europe as a feminine equivalent of   John  , but in England it has only been in common use as a vernacular given name since the 19th century. Celebrated British bearers of the name include the novelist  Joanna Trollope  (  b. 1943 ), the actress  Joanna Lumley  (  b. 1946 ), and the concert pianist  Joanna McGregor  (  b. 1959 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Joannah","meanings":["From the Latin form, <i>Io(h)anna</i>, of Greek <i>Iōanna</i>, the feminine equivalent of <i>Iōannēs</i> (  see  John  ). In the New Testament, this name is borne by a woman who was one of Jesus's followers (Luke 8:3; 24:10). She was the wife of the steward of the household of King Herod Antipas. The name was regularly used throughout the Middle Ages in most parts of Europe as a feminine equivalent of   John  , but in England it has only been in common use as a vernacular given name since the 19th century. Celebrated British bearers of the name include the novelist  Joanna Trollope  (  b. 1943 ), the actress  Joanna Lumley  (  b. 1946 ), and the concert pianist  Joanna McGregor  (  b. 1959 )."]},{"name":"Joana","meanings":["From the Latin form, <i>Io(h)anna</i>, of Greek <i>Iōanna</i>, the feminine equivalent of <i>Iōannēs</i> (  see  John  ). In the New Testament, this name is borne by a woman who was one of Jesus's followers (Luke 8:3; 24:10). She was the wife of the steward of the household of King Herod Antipas. The name was regularly used throughout the Middle Ages in most parts of Europe as a feminine equivalent of   John  , but in England it has only been in common use as a vernacular given name since the 19th century. Celebrated British bearers of the name include the novelist  Joanna Trollope  (  b. 1943 ), the actress  Joanna Lumley  (  b. 1946 ), and the concert pianist  Joanna McGregor  (  b. 1959 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ioanna Karatzaina was born in 1148, in İznik, Bursa, Türkiye, her father, Theodorus Kamateros, was 49 and her mother, Eufrosine Camaterina, was 51. She married Manuel Laskaris about 1168, in İznik, Bursa, Türkiye. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1186, in Istanbul, Fatih, İstanbul, Türkiye, at the age of 38."},"et":{"1148–1186":"1148–1186","1125–1195":"1125–1195","1140–1221":"1140–1221","1171–1221":"1171–1221","1171–1236":"1171–1236","1099–1180":"1099–1180","1097–Female":"1097–Surnud","1099":"1099","1186":"1186","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1195":"1195","1171":"1171","1180":"1180","1148":"1148","1236":"1236","1125":"1125","1221":"1221","about 1168":"umbes 1168","Abt 1171":"umbes 1171","Iznik, Bursa, Turkey":"İznik, Bursa, Türgi","Nicaea, Bursa, Turkey":"Bursa, Türgi","Istanbul, Fatih, İstanbul, Turquie":"Istanbul, Fatih, İstanbul, Türgi","Bulgaria, Bulgaria":"Bulgaaria","Byzantium (Constantinople), Istanbul, Turkey":"Istanbul, Fatih, İstanbul, Türgi"},"fi":{"1148–1186":"1148–1186","1125–1195":"1125–1195","1140–1221":"1140–1221","1171–1221":"1171–1221","1171–1236":"1171–1236","1099–1180":"1099–1180","1097–Female":"1097–Kuollut","1099":"1099","1186":"1186","1097":"1097","1140":"1140","1195":"1195","1171":"1171","1180":"1180","1148":"1148","1236":"1236","1125":"1125","1221":"1221","about 1168":"noin 1168","Abt 1171":"noin 1171","Iznik, Bursa, Turkey":"İznik, Bursa, Turkki","Nicaea, Bursa, Turkey":"Bursa, Turkki","Istanbul, Fatih, İstanbul, Turquie":"Istanbul, Fatih, İstanbul, Turkki","Bulgaria, Bulgaria":"Bulgaria","Byzantium (Constantinople), Istanbul, Turkey":"Istanbul, Fatih, İstanbul, Turkki"},"fr":{"1148–1186":"1148–1186","1125–1195":"1125–1195","1140–1221":"1140–1221","1171–1221":"1171–1221","1171–1236":"1171–1236","1099–1180